N:vibe-kanban
V:1.2.0
D:Visual Kanban board for AI agents. To Do->In Progress->Review->Done flow. Automatic git worktree isolation, MCP integration, and GitHub PR auto-generation. Supports remote deployment.
G:vibe-kanban kanban multi-agent git-worktree github-pr mcp task-management claude-code codex gemini docker remote
U[6]:
  Break epics into independent tasks and assign agents in parallel
  Visually track AI agent task status (To Do->Done)
  In the Review column, inspect diffs/logs via browser UI and retry if needed
  Combine GitHub PR-based team collaboration with AI agent execution
  Compare two agents on the same task (implementation comparison strategy)
  MCP integration allows agents to call board APIs directly
S[5]{n,action,details}:
  1,Start,npx vibe-kanban (or bash scripts/vibe-kanban-start.sh)
  2,CreateTask,Create a card on the board: title + description + agent selection
  3,Run,Drag a card to In Progress -> auto-start worktree + agent
  4,Review,Check diffs in the Review column -> approve or retry -> create PR
  5,MCP,Enable MCP server with --mcp flag -> agents can manipulate cards via API
R[5]:
  Keep card scope narrow (1 card = 1 commit)
  For tasks changing 2+ files, review the plan first with planno
  Use VIBE_KANBAN_REMOTE=true only on trusted networks
  If an agent stalls, reassign or split the card
  In MCP mode, control binding with MCP_HOST/MCP_PORT environment variables
E[4]{desc,in,out}:
  "Start server","npx vibe-kanban","Open board UI at http://localhost:3000"
  "Run agent","Drag card to In Progress","Create git worktree + run agent CLI + stream logs"
  "Create PR","Approve in Review column","Auto-create GitHub Draft PR + move card to Done"
  "MCP server","npx vibe-kanban --mcp","Expose card CRUD API via MCP protocol"
  "OpenCode ulw integration","Load ulw keyword + vibe-kanban then invoke task(category=\"visual-engineering\", run_in_background=True, ...) in parallel","Show concurrent Running status across 3 workspace Kanban boards"
T[3]{problem,solution}:
  "Worktree conflict","git worktree prune && git worktree list"
  "403 CORS error","Set VK_ALLOWED_ORIGINS=https://your-domain.com"
  "Port conflict","PORT=3001 npx vibe-kanban or lsof -i :3000"
